<Author>Bonita_Morenita
<Content>Would definitely stay again for business only. I checked into this hotel and my stay started off as a nightmare but ended well. I wound up staying here about a week. The night deskman was extremely rude and also would not give me a non-smoking room. He claimed there was nothing else available. There were also other guests at the front complaining of their smoking rooms when I checked in, but I thought it couldnt be that bad. When I got to the room, it smelled like the inside of an ashtray, the smoke smell was so strong I went to Walgreens at night after traveling all day just to buy Lysol and a Glade Plug In. After hours of trying to get settled in and sleep, this did not work. I called the front desk and requested another room, they still claimed nothing was available. At 3am my eyes were red and nose runny and throat itchy!!!! I had to call the front desk and threaten that I would have my CC company remove the charges because I literally couldn't breath or sleep and I would have to relocate to another hotel. I have had to stay in other smoking rooms before but this one was EXTREMELY bad. Not even opening the windows helped. I went to the front desk to get the keys for another room (suddenly there was availability), and the night deskman attempted to scold me like a child on how when I make a reservation I need to reserve a non-smoking room in advance. I was in disbelief!!! He was neither apologetic or even decent. He was upset that I had interrupted him at 3AM. I was the one moving my things in the middle of the night to the other side of the hotel with red eyes and a runny nose. This was the worse customer service I have ever received at a hotel in my life, and I'm a frequent business traveler. I would expect more from one of those charge by the hour roach motels. Needless to say, after that night I made it so I never had to go to the desk at night, and the women that were at the desk in the morning were extremely nice and helpful in every way possible. Also, the room that I was moved to was very decent and clean with a separate bedroom/living room. It had one of those motel smells, but this was a million times better than the previous room I had. The pool was small and very nice, especially in comparison to the hotel next door. There was hardly anyone at the pool. Next door there is a Sleep Inn and the pool was always full of families all day and night. There is also a BBQ grill at the pool with tables where you can cook and eat. The workout room was too warm and closet sized with only 2 machines. Luckily, I ran at the park down the street instead. Behind the hotel, about a block away, there is a very nice neighborhood park with lots of runners, golfers, bikers. It's surprising because you can't see any of this from the street, it all seems industrial and a bit ghetto looking from the main road, but if you walk down the street there are nice houses. The breakfast was comical. EVERYTHING was frozen and I would get to breakfast when it was ending everyday and the items were still frozen around 9am. There were frozen pancakes, english muffins, bagles, and bread etc., all hard as a rock. There was a toaster, but you had to microwave the breads before toasting them LOL. They literally had ice frozen on top of them as if they'd been in the freezer for weeks/months. There were 3 choices for cold cereal, and as I recall no fruit because I don't remember ever eating any and that would normally be my breakfast choice. There was orange juice and I believe apple juice also. Also microwave oatmeal. It was laughable, but at least they had something I guess. There were restaurants in the immediate area such as McDonalds, Taco Bell, a dine-in Pizza hut with salad bar(walking distance) and an IHOP (walking distance). I would only recommend this hotel for business travelers or people trying to save money with a family. I got an amazing deal on Priceline for this hotel. I would definitely stay here again but only at a severely discounted rate. Also, again, the desk manager on the night of my check-in, should not be in the hospitatlity business, PERIOD. I felt like I was being punk'd. 
