<Author>Kristinesonja
<Content>Good one night stay for business, quite happy! I had business at a conference at the Sheraton .2 miles down the road but couldn't get a room there. So, I had to look for alternatives. I was pleased with the close locations. I found security gates, so wondered what that was about. But seeing the room was a pleasant surprise. The room was a non smoking king bed room and still very large with lots of room. A sofa was in front with a sitting area and a nice kitchen area. This included a full size fridge, coffee pot, toaster and more. A nice little kitchen seating area with high stools, great for working. The bath was more than adequate with a long counter. The closet had lots more room than usual, an extra pillow and extra blanket. The room was clean and king bed was comfortable. I think i was most impressed with the open space in the room, spacious. My only disappointment was that they charged my $5 for the internet hook up. We drove the 6 or 7 miles east for dinner on Lincoln Avenue, pleasant evening, easy drive. I was pleased with the room and it's location worked out great for me to have easy access to the Sheraton. The other disappointment, when it came to breakfast, the choices for something close was very poor. Still good place to stay. 
