<Author>SWINGLINE34
<Content>Only if you're desperate! I had originally reserved a room at another hotel (AmeriSuites Miami/Airport West) but that hotel transferred my reservation to this hotel because they were going to be doing some construction. It just so happened that this was the same dates of the big Miami Boat Show Convention and I suspect they wanted to boot me because I was getting a discounted rate. Back to the Homestead. This place is not your average hotel. This hotel is substandard! They did have an airport shuttle but the driver couldn't speak english and I thought the old van they picked me up in wouldn't make it back to the hotel in one piece. The batteries in the tv remote were dead and corroding in the remote. The shelf in the closet was falling out of the wall. The place was noisy with the other residents blasting music in the parking lot from their car stereos. At night, some of the other residents were still blasting latino music from their room after 11pm. I called the front desk to complain and an answering machine answered and advised that the front desk was closed for the night. Apparently it's not manned overnight. It did give me the option of pushing 1 to be transferred to a person. I did so and the person who answered advised that no personnel was on site overnight. She said that if I could tell her which room the music was coming from, she'd call them by telephone and ask them to turn it down. I calmly explained to her that I was in bed for the night, not dressed, and wasn't going to walk the hotel to find out which room it was. Keep in mind this is an open air hotel where your room door opens to the outside parking lot. Not the safest of all the set-ups. Don't let your women stay here alone! This place was liveable but sub-standard for a hotel. Look elsewhere for a hotel unless you have no choice. 
