<Content>One star Thought I got a good deal on Priceline on a hotel near Miami airport for a 1-night pre-cruise stay.But this hotel is a $30 cab ride from the airport and a $25 cab ride from the seaport.Two stories. No elevators. No porters. So had to carry my three heavy bags up stairs myself.The renovated room looked like it had been renovated with used appliances, cabinets, furniture from the 1980s.The bed was hard. The pillows were flat.The front desk was understaffed. The only person there was on the phone for 20 minutes giving a caller directions...After giving me my key card, he just pointed me toward the door, still on the phone.The only good thing about the room were the linens, which were clean.There was no vending area and no on-site restaurant. A Tony Roma's is a few hundred yards away.Next time, I'll know better. 
