<Author>Eric-A95
<Content>Gross First, we were bumped across Miami from one Homestead property to another, which added an hour of driving. Then, after arriving at this place, my fiancee went to the bathroom and almost threw up. The room looked as though it had just been cleaned -- the beds were made, and the bathroom was relatively fresh -- except for the toilet. It seemed as though a staffer had cleaned and then gone to the bathroom -- wrong order!Yes, he or she had flushed after going #2, but fecal matter was stuck to the toilet. There were also many hairs all over the bathroom. This was simply unacceptable. The in-room kitchen was old and unrenovated. If you need to live in a motel, this might be a good deal, but as travelers, we did not enjoy this. Unfortunately, after driving all over Miami, we were too tired to move again. Once we checked the beds and found them clean, we decided to brave it until morning. All told, it was a decent value, but you get what you pay for! 
