<Content>Excellent Place I got this hotel for a low Priceline bid and I was very happy with it. It appears to be a new place. Not shopworn at all. It's an extended stay hotel so it has a fairly complete kitchen with full sized frig, microwave, etc. It was a little hard to find at night. The main entrance is about half a block off the main road and the entrance at that point as well as the hotel has no signage indicating that it's the Homestead. Wireless Internet is $5 a day and worked well although they block access to MSN Messenger perhaps to block free long distance phone calls over the Internet. This seems to be fairly normal at these hotels. No complaints! I'd be happy to stay there anytime. 
