<Content>Worst stay ever!!!! Don't stay here Booked this hotel on priceline and called the hotel to make sure that we would be able to accomodate 3 people in our room. The woman at the desk told us that she would note our reservation for a rollaway. We arrived after many airline delays at 1 a.m. and on arrival the man at the desk told us that he didn't have any rollaways and that my 15 year old could sleep on the couch. We get up to the room and there is no couch! So we call the desk and ask once again where our daughter is supposed to sleep. The man states that suddenly he has a rollaway but no mattress for it and he'll call us back. He calls us back and says he has the rollaway and that he would be right over with it. He showed up about 20 minutes later with the rollaway and some sheets. No pillow, no blankets. He went on to tell me that since this was a priceline room that I couldn't expect my daughter to have anywhere to sleep. The next morning my husband spoke with the General Manager who again commented on it being a priceline room and offered a free one night stay coupon. Meanwhile we had a leak on the floor in the kitchen which caused the floor to be wet and slippery and bugs (hundreds of small ants and tiny bugs) on the counters. The chairs, counters and floor were sticky. The final straw came when it was discovered that the towels in the bathroom had been used - full of black hair and stained. We would never even consider staying here again and suggest that you don't either. 
