<Author>A TripAdvisor Member
<Content>Pleasant Experience My partner and I, after months of planning our first ever vacation, decided to stay to the Miami Airport Homestead Suites. We were greeted pleasantly by the hotel. We spent a total of 2 weeks there and had a blast. We did have 2 negative experiences though. FIRST - The hotel apparently has a policy for extended stays; they give you 1 full clean a week and 1 refresh. After coming to terms with that not so pleasing policy we decided to stay on. To our dismay, our rooms, after a full 8 days, had NOT even received ONE cleaning. After complaining to the front desk with no response, we finally resorted to the Manager and our room was immediately placed in order. SECOND - we had a situation with our credit card - and the hotel's way of dealing with the situation was to lock our room in our absence. Whilst I was shopping, my partner came back to find the key to the room not functioning. They refused to let him into the room to get the cash which we had stored there. They claimed that he was not on the guest list - DUHHH the room WAS booked for 2 and 2 persons showed up at checkin. Be sure to include all roomers on the guest list. After that, we got every request we had (that is after putting the manager in his place). There was ONE really nice lady at the front desk who usually worked the late shift. YOU can stay there! it's pretty close to shopping and the airport but you'll need a rental (depots are close to the hotel too). Great time in Miami. 
